We first oriented the images of photoconverted spot in Imaris to get a view perpendicular to the spot in each time frame, and cropped around the spot. These images were then manually thresholded by Image J (path: Image - > Adjust - > Threshold) to account for photobleaching and then converted into binary images. From these binarized images, we used the standard deviation of the white pixel distribution along the medial-lateral and anterior-posterior axes as measures of the medial-lateral width and anterior-posterior height of the photoconverted spot respectively. These metrics were measured by a custom Matlab code provided below:for k = 1:8 
filename = strcat('SLICE', num2str(k), '.tif'); 
